          "items": [
            {
              "metadata": {
                "label": "'join",
                "description": "Joins zero or more strings together with a separator.\n\n```ballerina\nstring:'join(\" \", \"Ballerina\", \"is\", \"a\", \"programming\", \"language\") ⇒ Ballerina is a programming language\nstring[] array = [\"John\", \"23\", \"USA\", \"Computer Science\", \"Swimmer\"];\nstring:'join(\",\", ...array) ⇒ John,23,USA,Computer Science,Swimmer\n```\n",
                "icon": "https://bcentral-packageicons.azureedge.net/images/ballerina_lang.string_0.0.0.png"
              },
              "codedata": {
                "node": "FUNCTION_CALL",
                "org": "ballerina",
                "module": "lang.string",
                "packageName": "lang.string",
                "symbol": "'join",
                "version": "0.0.0"
              },
              "enabled": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "metadata": {
            "label": "lang.array",
            "description": "",
            "keywords": []
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "metadata": {
                "label": "'map",
                "description": "Applies a function to each member of an array and returns an array of the results.\n\n```ballerina\nint[] numbers = [0, 1, 2];\nnumbers.map(n => n * 2) ⇒ [0,2,4]\n```\n",
                "icon": "https://bcentral-packageicons.azureedge.net/images/ballerina_lang.array_0.0.0.png"
              },
              "codedata": {
                "node": "FUNCTION_CALL",
                "org": "ballerina",
                "module": "lang.array",
                "packageName": "lang.array",
                "symbol": "'map",
                "version": "0.0.0"
              },
              "enabled": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "metadata": {
            "label": "lang.stream",
            "description": "",
            "keywords": []
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "metadata": {
                "label": "'map",
                "description": "Applies a function to each member of a stream and returns a stream of the results.\n\n```ballerina\nstream<float> ms = [14.5f, 45.5f, 6.8f, 4f].toStream();\nstream<float> cms = ms.map(m => m * 100.0);\ncms.next() ⇒ {\"value\":1450.0}\n```\n",
                "icon": "https://bcentral-packageicons.azureedge.net/images/ballerina_lang.stream_0.0.0.png"
              },
              "codedata": {
                "node": "FUNCTION_CALL",
                "org": "ballerina",
                "module": "lang.stream",
                "packageName": "lang.stream",
                "symbol": "'map",
                "version": "0.0.0"
              },
              "enabled": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "metadata": {
            "label": "lang.map",
            "description": "",
            "keywords": []
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "metadata": {
                "label": "'map",
                "description": "Applies a function each member of a map and returns a map of the result.\n\nThe resulting map will have the same keys as the argument map.\n\n```ballerina\nmap<int> marks = {\"Carl\": 85, \"Bob\": 50, \"Max\": 60};\nmarks.map(m => m > 50) ⇒ {\"Carl\":true,\"Bob\":false,\"Max\":true}\n```\n",
                "icon": "https://bcentral-packageicons.azureedge.net/images/ballerina_lang.map_0.0.0.png"
              },
              "codedata": {
                "node": "FUNCTION_CALL",
                "org": "ballerina",
                "module": "lang.map",
                "packageName": "lang.map",
                "symbol": "'map",
                "version": "0.0.0"
              },
              "enabled": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "metadata": {
            "label": "lang.table",
            "description": "",
            "keywords": []
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "metadata": {
                "label": "'map",
                "description": "Applies a function to each member of a table and returns a table of the result.\n\n```ballerina\ntable<record {|int id; int math; int physics;|}> students = table [\n    {id: 1, math: 78, physics: 70},\n    {id: 2, math: 83, physics: 80}\n];\nstudents.map(student => {id: student.id, avg: (student.math + student.physics) / 2}) ⇒ [{\"id\":1,\"avg\":74},{\"id\":2,\"avg\":81}]\n```\n",
                "icon": "https://bcentral-packageicons.azureedge.net/images/ballerina_lang.table_0.0.0.png"
              },
              "codedata": {
                "node": "FUNCTION_CALL",
                "org": "ballerina",
                "module": "lang.table",
                "packageName": "lang.table",
                "symbol": "'map",
                "version": "0.0.0"
              },
              "enabled": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
