              "metadata": {
                "label": "'map",
                "description": "Applies a function to each item in an xml sequence, and returns an xml sequence of the results.\n\nEach item is represented as a singleton value.\n\n```ballerina\nxml x = xml `<book>Hamlet</book><book>Macbeth</book>`;\nx.map(function (xml xmlContent) returns xml => \n  xml `<book kind=\"play\">${xmlContent.children()}</book>`\n) ⇒ <book kind=\"play\">Hamlet</book><book kind=\"play\">Macbeth</book>\n```\n",
                "icon": "https://bcentral-packageicons.azureedge.net/images/ballerina_lang.xml_0.0.0.png"
              },
              "codedata": {
                "node": "FUNCTION_CALL",
                "org": "ballerina",
